<p>Chicago's cold climate demands robust HVAC systems capable of handling temperature extremes from sub-zero winters to hot, humid summers. For air conditioning, systems with SEER ratings of 16-20 provide optimal efficiency for the region's cooling demands, typically running from May through September. Heat pumps can be effective but require backup heating systems for Chicago's harsh winters when temperatures frequently drop below their effective operating range.</p>

