<p>Chicago residents have access to several attractive incentives for solar and HVAC installations. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on the total cost of solar installations through 2032, then steps down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to the full system cost including equipment, installation, and permitting fees.</p>

<p>Illinois offers additional state-level incentives through the Adjustable Block Program, which provides Solar Renewable Energy Credits (SRECs) that can add \$1,000-\$2,000 in value to typical residential installations. The Illinois Solar for All program provides additional benefits for income-qualified residents, including potential grants covering up to 100% of installation costs.</p>

